-- Suzlon Energy Gains to Two-Week High as HSBC Holdings Raises to `Neutral'
-- B y   M a r g o   T o w i e
-- 2011-02-08T03:48:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-08/suzlon-energy-gains-to-two-week-high-as-hsbc-holdings-raises-to-neutral-.html
  Suzlon Energy Ltd . rose 2 percent to
50.5 rupees as of 9:16 a.m. in Mumbai, set for its highest close
since Jan. 25. The world’s third-biggest maker of wind turbines
was raised to “neutral” from ‘‘underweight” by Shishir Singh,
an analyst at HSBC Holdings Plc.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
